# Topic to fill the gaps Siarhei's gaps

## How to properly define ASRs, Quality Attributes

### Best practices to define requirements and quality attributes and relook ASR(s) gaps
  - Quality attribute, ASRs, Goals should be SMART
    - Measurable
    - Reachable
    - Specific
    - Relevant
    - Time-Bound
  - Quality attributes can be defined with quality attributes scenrions
    - [Example of QAS](https://people.ece.ubc.ca/matei/EECE417/BASS/ch04lev1sec4.html)
  - Explain how to map quality attributes and requirements
    - Need to explain how to isolate quality attributes from each other with fixed other quality attributes regarding target quality attribute
## Techniques to perform pros and cons analysis
  - How to create and prioritize analysis creterias
    - How to assign different weight for the criterias
  - Quality attributes pros and cons analysis table example
  - Compare solutions based on quality attributes
  - Alternative frameworks
    - [SWOT analysis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SWOT_analysis)
    - [Pareto Analysis (80/20 Rule)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pareto_principle)
    - [Force Field Analysis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Force-field_analysis)
    - [The Delphi Technique](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Delphi_method)
    - [Mind Mapping](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mind_map)
    - [Scenario Planning](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scenario_planning)
    - [Decision Trees](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decision_tree)
    - [Risk Analysis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk_analysis_(business))
    - [Multi-Criteria Decision Analysis (MCDA)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiple-criteria_decision_analysis)
  
